---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  active="get-involved"
  title="Get involved — storytree"
  description="Why storytree is built out in the open, how it tries to keep itself honest, what it commits to, and how to take part. Invite-only for now — but the door to ask is wide open."
>
  <!-- intro -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">Get involved</p>
      <h1>Why this exists — and how to take part.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        storytree is more than a tool — it's a bet about how software gets built once AI&nbsp;agents
        write most of the code. If that bet resonates, here's where we are, how we try to keep
        ourselves honest, what we commit to, and how to come in.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- the bet -->
  <section class="section--tight">
    <div class="wrap band">
      <div class="band__inner">
        <p class="eyebrow">The bet</p>
        <h2>An open record is a stronger foundation for trust than promises.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Most projects ask you to trust the people running them. We're trying to show you don't have
          to. When agents write most of the code and humans can't read all of it, the thing that keeps
          a project honest isn't good intentions — it's a complete, open record you can interrogate
          directly. If that works, it's a fairer way to build software, and one more people can take
          part in. If it doesn't, you'll be able to see that too.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- how we keep ourselves honest -->
  <section class="section--tight">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we keep ourselves honest</p>
      <h2>An open record — and, where we're headed, one you can just ask.</h2>
      <p>
        Every decision and the reasoning behind it is kept on the record, not summarised away after
        the fact. That's the foundation of the whole trust model: you don't have to take anyone's word,
        because you can check. There's an honest gap today — the people running storytree could still
        quietly edit that record — and we say so plainly. We're closing it: making the record
        append-only and tamper-evident, so even we can't rewrite history unseen (the foundation for
        this already exists). And we're building toward the strongest version of the idea: a way to
        simply <strong>ask the project</strong>, in plain language, against its whole record — so any
        hidden agenda has to survive being asked about directly.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        We'll only ever claim the parts that are actually built. Where something is still ahead of us,
        you'll hear "this is where we're headed," not a wall that isn't there yet.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- the constitution -->
  <section class="section--tight">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">What we commit to</p>
      <h2>The constitution.</h2>
      <p>
        What storytree believes, and how it plans to keep itself honest, lives in one place — written
        plainly. It's a living draft; it'll change as we learn. But it's the thing to hold us to.
      </p>
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/constitution/">Read the constitution →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- where we are + come in -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose front">
      <p class="eyebrow">Where we are right now</p>
      <h2>Early, honest, and growing slowly.</h2>
      <p>
        storytree isn't open source yet — it's not ready to be. Taking part is invite-only while we
        iterate out the rough edges and build the guardrails real openness needs. Today one person
        still decides what gets built next — we're honest that "your voice counts" isn't yet "your
        vote counts." But this website is the open front door: you're welcome to watch, to ask hard
        questions, and to tell us where we're wrong — that last one especially.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__cta">
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/contact/">Ask to come in →</a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/how-it-works/">See how it works</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero__cta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.7rem; margin-top: 1.6rem; }
  .front h2 { margin-top: 0.2rem; }

  .band {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2f6b3f 0%, #245031 100%);
    border-radius: calc(var(--radius) + 4px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }
  .band::after {
    content: ""; position: absolute; inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(420px 300px at 92% -20%, rgba(169,200,127,0.30), transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(360px 260px at 0% 120%, rgba(214,178,113,0.22), transparent 60%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .band__inner { position: relative; padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); max-width: 46rem; }
  .band .eyebrow { color: #f2cd92; }
  .band h2 { color: #fdf6ec; margin-bottom: 0.7rem; }
  .band .lede { color: #e7ecdf; }
</style>
